  "response": "Here are steps to hire owner operators:\n\n1. Recruitment Channels\n- Online job boards\n- Trucking industry websites\n- Social media platforms\n- Industry trade publications\n- Referral programs\n- Trucking industry events\n\n2. Screening Process\n- Verify commercial driver's license (CDL)\n- Review driving history\n- Check safety records\n- Confirm insurance coverage\n- Inspect truck and equipment\n- Verify DOT compliance\n\n3. Evaluation Criteria\n- Years of experience\n- Clean driving record\n- Equipment condition\n- Business reliability\n- References\n- Specific route/cargo expertise\n\n4. Communication & Negotiation\n- Clearly define contract terms\n- Discuss compensation structure\n- Outline expectations\n- Explain payment schedules\n- Review performance metrics\n\n5. Legal Considerations\n- Independent contractor agreement\n- Insurance requirements\n- Tax documentation\n- Compliance with transportation regulations\n\n6. Onboarding\n- Orientation process\n- Training on company procedures\n- Integration with dispatch system\n- Communication protocols\n\n7. Ongoing Management\n- Performance monitoring\n- Regular communication\n- Fair compensation\n- Continued relationship building\n\n8. Additional Recommendations\n- Background checks\n- Motor vehicle record checks\n- Drug screening",
